.SH "NAME"
inkf \- Yet Another Network Kanji Filter
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
inkf \fB[\-jescblwWJESCBmMOLtf]\fR \fB[\fR\fIfile ...\fR\fB]\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBinkf\fR is a yet another kanji code converter among networks, like nkf.
It converts input kanji code to designated kanji code
such as \s-1ISO\-2022\-JP,\s0 Shift_JIS, EUC\-JP, EUC\-KR, \s-1UTF\-7, UTF\-8, UTF\-16\s0, \s-1UTF\-32, \s-1GB2312 or BIG5.\s0
.PP
One of the most unique faculty of \fBinkf\fR is the guess of the input kanji encodings.
It currently recognizes \s-1ISO\-2022\-JP,\s0 Shift_JIS, EUC\-JP, EUC\-KR \s-1UTF\-8, UTF\-16\s0, \s-1UTF\-32 and \s-1GB2312.\s0
So users needn't set the input kanji code explicitly.
.PP
